      "content": "You don't need to spend fifty years scraping together a shadow; you can simply stop pretending to be the person you thought you were and let the rest of your life begin in the present moment. The people who respected you in the past will eventually respect the person who is alive today, even if they don't understand the loss. It is a mercy to release the burden of a lie rather than carry a heavy, hollow identity for the rest of your days.",
      "source": "target",
